DirBuster
Multi-threaded GUI web directory brute-forcer

Web Application
Description
DirBuster is a multi-threaded Java application designed to brute force directories and files on web servers. It has a GUI interface and supports various brute-forcing methods.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which dirbuster
Install command:

sudo apt install dirbuster
Basic Syntax
dirbuster (GUI application)
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
dirbuster

Launch DirBuster GUI	Starting web directory brute-forcing	
Set Target URL in GUI

Configure target website	First step after launching	
Select wordlist: /usr/share/dirbuster/wordlists/

Choose wordlist for attack	Configuring the attack dictionary	
Set threads (10-50 recommended)

Configure parallel connections	Balancing speed vs server load	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Launch DirBuster from menu or terminal
2
Enter target URL
3
Select a wordlist
4
Set number of threads
5
Click Start
6
Monitor progress and results
7
Export findings when done
Understanding the Output
Results show found directories and files with response codes. Tree view shows the website structure discovered.

Important Warnings
•
GUI-based tool - requires X11 display
•
High thread counts can DoS the target
•
Only use on authorized targets
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
